3VAR: a complicated system than most of the Algol-type stars, i.e., compact triple system with separation of the components

5VAR: nated components D and E, inferred on the basis of an apparent 32 year apsidal motion, are now considered spurious.

7VAR: greater distances from A. ADS 2362A, EA 2.12 - 3.40V, 2.86732442d, abrupt period changes. Orbital and rotation periods
